{"lemma":"وَضُوءِ","slug":"وَضُوءِ","root":"#.ض.#","root_slug":"_-ض-_","root_link":"/words/roots/_-ض-_","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":5},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n42008","n42009"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%88%D9%8E%D8%B6%D9%8F%D9%88%D8%A1%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of وَضُؤَ (waḍuʔa) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of تَوَضَّأَ (tawaḍḍaʔa) (form V)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"cleanness"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"wudu, ablution","tags":["broadly"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"water used in ablution"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/wu.dˤuːʔ/","/wa.dˤuːʔ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n42008","headword_ar":"وَضُوْءٌ","root":"wDA^","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wuDuwo'N","text_ar":"وُضُوْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n42009","headword_ar":"وُضُوْءٌ","root":"wDA^","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"signifies The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"act of ablution, &c."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) (see 5); and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waDuwo'N","text_ar":"وَضُوْءٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"water with which that act is performed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"water that is prepared for that act,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, TA,) and is said to be also an inf. n., [or rather a quasi-inf. n., signifying the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"act itself"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, K:) or they are syn. words of two different dialects, each sometimes used as an inf. n., signifying the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"act,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(though inf. ns. of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEuwlN","text_ar":"فَعُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"deviate from constant rule, TA,) and each sometimes as signifying the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"water."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, TA.) AA says, that ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waDuwo'N","text_ar":"وَضُوْءٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies “ the water with which one performs the ablution above mentioned; ” and he knew not"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wuDuwo'N","text_ar":"وُضُوْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[though it occurs in many traditions]: and A 'Obeyd disallows"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waDuwo'N","text_ar":"وَضُوْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and allows only ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waDuwo'N","text_ar":"وَضُوْءٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}